Examine this procedure: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE INSERT_TEAM (V_ID in
NUMBER, V_CITY in VARCHAR2 DEFAULT 'AUSTIN', V_NAME in VARCHAR2) IS
BEGIN INSERT INTO TEAM (id, city, name) VALUES (v_id, v_city, v_name); COMMIT;
END; Which two statements will successfully invoke this procedure in SQL*Plus? (Choose
two.)
A. EXECUTE INSERT_TEAM;
B. EXECUTE INSERT_TEAM(3, V_NAME=&gt;'LONGHORNS', V_CITY=&gt;'AUSTIN');
C. EXECUTE INSERT_TEAM(3,'AUSTIN','LONGHORNS');
D. EXECUTE INSERT_TEAM (V_ID := 3, V_NAME := 'LONGHORNS', V_CITY :=
'AUSTIN');
E. EXECUTE INSERT_TEAM (3,'LONGHORNS');
Answer: B,C
